    realWorldExample: "Classic interview trap: 'design a URL shortener' without clarifying — candidate designs globally distributed with 99.999% availability. Interviewer meant a simple internal tool for 100 engineers. 5 minutes of clarification would have revealed: single-region, 100 RPS, no availability SLA needed. Completely different design.",
    interviewQuestion: "What are the most important questions to ask before designing a notification system?",
    modelAnswer: "1) Scale: how many notifications/day? (100M? affects queue choice). 2) Types: push, email, SMS, in-app? 3) Delivery guarantee: at-least-once or exactly-once? (SMS billing: exactly-once matters). 4) Latency: real-time (<1s) or best-effort (within 5 min)? 5) User preferences: do users opt out? per-type settings? 6) Order matters? (chat messages must be ordered, alerts don't). These answers determine architecture.",
