    modelAnswer: "1) Recognize the pattern: is it feed-like, storage-heavy, real-time messaging, location-based, or search? 2) Apply the canonical architecture for that pattern. 3) Adapt for the specific constraints (scale, consistency, features). Most novel questions are combinations of known patterns (e.g., 'design a real-time collaborative editing tool' = WebSocket + CRDT + conflict-free merge).",
